I've encountered a weird issue using the MapBox visualization - if anyone has any insight, i'd appreciate it.

Basically there's one set of data (A) that isn't showing up.  If I filter on it nothing appears.  If I filter on it and something else in a diffent location (B), B appears.

Looking at the JSON response for the chart, everything seems fine.  Data is returned for each.  Here is an example point for each:

*A*
```{
	"type": "Feature",
	"properties": {
		"metric": 3632,
		"radius": null
	},
	"geometry": {
		"type": "Point",
		"coordinates": [-79.3831843, 43.653226]
	}
}```
*B*
```{
	"type": "Feature",
	"properties": {
		"metric": 11,
		"radius": null
	},
	"geometry": {
		"type": "Point",
		"coordinates": [-61.0118426, 45.5137315]
	}
}```
A has 184 points.  A and B together have 1416 points.

Full disclosure, I did not setup this chart, I'm just trying to debug it.  I've tried a number of things:
1. I offset all longitude and latitudes to determine if it was a bug for those particular values; same result.
2. I zoomed in on the area to see if it was just tiny; same result.
3. A and B together have a lot more data points, so I reduced the time range to make sure it still worked with fewer data points; same result.
I'm not really sure where to go from here.  I guess my next step is to track down and dig into the visualization code, but I'd prefer to avoid that if I'm just doing something foolish.

Thanks!

